: {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wNC0yNFQxMTo0MDozN1rOGLTqIg==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wNC0yNFQxMjowMzowOFrOGLUbAw==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQxNDUwOTYwMg==", "bodyText": "Trailing newline? I don't care, but some others do.\n\"below\", \"or higher\", etc. are ambiguous terms for log levels.\nAnother common problem is very chatty loggers and the resulting system load just handling log messages.\nIt's not guaranteed that no plugins log credentials on INFO anyway.\nInconsistent terminology: Log recorder vs. logger.\n\n\n  \n    \n      \n        Suggested change\n        \n          \n    \n\n        \n      \n    \n    \n      \n          \n            \n            fine_warning=Creating a log recorder at FINE level or below may expose secrets in the logs. It is recommended that you delete the logger when you no longer need it.\n          \n          \n            \n            fine_warning=Loggers that record messages at FINE, FINER, or even FINEST can cause performance issues when many messages are being logged. Additionally, more verbose log levels increase the likelihood of credentials being logged. It is recommended that you delete such loggers, or update them to a less verbose level, when you no longer need them.", "url": "https://github.com/jenkinsci/jenkins/pull/4530#discussion_r414509602", "createdAt": "2020-04-24T11:40:37Z", "author": {"login": "daniel-beck"}, "path": "core/src/main/resources/hudson/logging/LogRecorder/configure.properties", "diffHunk": "@@ -0,0 +1 @@\n+fine_warning=Creating a log recorder at FINE level or below may expose secrets in the logs. It is recommended that you delete the logger when you no longer need it.", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "30d3b0b3b578d5e6572dc04fd2ff8fe57928c393"}, "originalPosition": 1}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQxNDUwOTk4Ng==", "bodyText": "Links from Jenkins to jenkins.io should always use URLs in redirect/ to be future-proof.", "url": "https://github.com/jenkinsci/jenkins/pull/4530#discussion_r414509986", "createdAt": "2020-04-24T11:41:14Z", "author": {"login": "daniel-beck"}, "path": "core/src/main/resources/hudson/logging/LogRecorder/configure.jelly", "diffHunk": "@@ -27,9 +27,16 @@ THE SOFTWARE.\n -->\n <?jelly escape-by-default='true'?>\n <j:jelly xmlns:j=\"jelly:core\" xmlns:st=\"jelly:stapler\" xmlns:d=\"jelly:define\" xmlns:l=\"/lib/layout\" xmlns:t=\"/lib/hudson\" xmlns:f=\"/lib/form\">\n-<l:layout>\n+<l:layout permission=\"${app.ADMINISTER}\" title=\"${%Configure Log Recorder}\">\n   <st:include page=\"sidepanel.jelly\" />\n   <l:main-panel>\n+    <h1>${%Configure log recorder} <t:help href=\"https://jenkins.io/doc/book/system-administration/viewing-logs/#logs-in-jenkins\" /></h1>", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "30d3b0b3b578d5e6572dc04fd2ff8fe57928c393"}, "originalPosition": 8}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQxNDUyMjExNQ==", "bodyText": "Redundant given https://github.com/jenkinsci/jenkins/pull/4530/files#diff-cb8b7584e7a539c988ae99e9951f7b65R213 and https://github.com/jenkinsci/jenkins/pull/4530/files?w=1#diff-fcc5c10b76c1e25e4ac9caae4fa96acfR71 ?", "url": "https://github.com/jenkinsci/jenkins/pull/4530#discussion_r414522115", "createdAt": "2020-04-24T12:03:08Z", "author": {"login": "daniel-beck"}, "path": "core/src/main/java/hudson/logging/LogRecorder.java", "diffHunk": "@@ -401,6 +407,8 @@ public synchronized void doDoDelete(StaplerResponse rsp) throws IOException, Ser\n      * RSS feed for log entries.\n      */\n     public void doRss( StaplerRequest req, StaplerResponse rsp ) throws IOException, ServletException {\n+        Jenkins.get().checkPermission(Jenkins.SYSTEM_READ);", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "30d3b0b3b578d5e6572dc04fd2ff8fe57928c393"}, "originalPosition": 40}]}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", 